I&#39;ll include it anyway in case others wonder what I mean by an automated
build process that keeps the JavaDoc and code in sync:

    &lt;target name=&quot;all&quot; depends=&quot;compile,test,doc&quot;/&gt;

    &lt;target name=&quot;doc&quot;&gt;

        &lt;javadoc packagenames=&quot;com.whatever.*&quot;
            sourcepath=&quot;${src.dir}&quot;
            destdir=&quot;${docs.dir}/api&quot;
            author=&quot;true&quot;
            version=&quot;true&quot;
            windowtitle=&quot;${Name} API&quot;
            doctitle=&quot;${Name} API&quot;
            bottom=&quot;${copyright}&quot;&gt;
        &lt;/javadoc&gt;

    &lt;/target&gt;

